{"type":"message","id":"646cd502","parentId":"9cab0578","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:27:03.108Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_tlilqq7dubdg_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 042615\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: tic/tic_classifier.ps1 (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what single concrete action would best advance the goals.\r\n\r\nLooking at the pending items:\r\n1. Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n2. Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\r\n3. Tune λ empirically (start: λ=0.7)\r\n4. Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n5. Measure compression ratio: original vs. summarized pulse\r\n\r\nAnd the NEXT ACTION for the TIC Experiment:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe key insight from this session is \"COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\" - that Problem 1 (Compression) and Problem 2 (Causal Discovery) are the SAME problem.\r\n\r\nGiven that I need to take ONE concrete action, the most impactful next step seems to be setting up the TIC experiment framework. The immediate practical step would be to:\r\n\r\n1. Create a script or document that outlines the TIC experiment methodology\r\n2. This could be a PowerShell script to analyze pulse logs, or documentation defining the approach\r\n\r\nLet me look at what would be most useful. The TIC classifier needs to be implemented. A practical first step would be to create a script that:\r\n- Reads the pulse log files\r\n- Extracts content for comparison\r\n- Sets up the framework for invariant/variant classification\r\n\r\nSince I need to be specific and prefer file edits, I should either:\r\n1. Create a new script file for the TIC experiment\r\n2. Update an existing file with the implementation\r\n\r\nThe most concrete action would be to create the TIC classifier script that will analyze the pulse logs. This moves us toward the next action item directly.\r\n\r\nLet me check if there's an existing scripts directory or if I should create the script in a new location.\r\n\r\nGiven the Phase 1 advancement focus on TIC experiment, the most impactful single action is to create the TIC classifier script or implement the experiment framework.\r\n\r\n\r\nI'll craft a PowerShell script to perform the initial TIC analysis on the pulse log files. This will involve reading the logs, extracting key content, and preparing the groundwork for invariant/variant classification.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the critical next step for Phase 1, but there's no implementation yet to analyze the pulse logs for invariant/variant patterns. The theory is solid; we need the tool to test it.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier script that will analyze pulse logs, extract invariant/variant content patterns, and measure classification accuracy against the success criteria (>70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n# Phase 1 Experiment: Compression-Causal Duality Validation\r\n# Created: 2026-03-24\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$LookbackCount = 20,\r\n    [string]$LogDir = \"logs\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\n# Load pulse history\r\n$pulseFiles = Get-ChildItem -Path $LogDir -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | Sort-Object Name -Descending | Select-Object -First $LookbackCount\r\n\r\nif ($pulseFiles.Count -lt 3) {\r\n    Write-Host \"[TIC] Insufficient pulse logs ($($pulseFiles.Count) found, need 3+)\"\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"[TIC] Analyzing $($pulseFiles.Count) pulse logs for invariant/variant patterns\"\r\n\r\n# Extract content from each pulse\r\n$pulses = @()\r\nforeach ($file in $pulseFiles) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $file.FullName -Raw\r\n    $pulses += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n        Name = $file.Name\r\n        Content = $content\r\n        Words = ($content -split '\\s+').Count\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# === Invariant Detection ===\r\n# Invariants = patterns that persist across pulses (goals, architecture, core beliefs)\r\n# Variants = patterns that change between pulses (timestamps, specific results, ephemeral states)\r\n\r\n$invariantIndicators = @(\r\n    \"Phase\", \"Architecture\", \"Goal\", \"Complete\", \"Pending\",\r\n    \"insight\", \"synthesis\", \"hypothesis\", \"theory\",\r\n    \"Compression\", \"Temporal\", \"Invariant\", \"Causal\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$variantIndicators = @(\r\n    \"timestamp\", \"2026-03-\", \"[0-9]{6}\", \"pulse_\",\r\n    \"Last updated\", \"Created:\", \"Observation:\", \"Action:\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n# Count invariant vs variant patterns per pulse\r\n$analysis = @()\r\nfor ($i = 0; $i -lt $pulses.Count; $i++) {\r\n    $pulse = $pulses[$i]\r\n    $invariantCount = 0\r\n    $variantCount = 0\r\n    \r\n    foreach ($indicator in $invariantIndicators) {\r\n        $invariantCount += ([regex]::Matches($pulse.Content, $indicator, [System.Text.RegularExpressions.RegexOptions]::IgnoreCase)).Count\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    foreach ($indicator in $variantIndicators) {\r\n        $variantCount += ([regex]::Matches($pulse.Content, $indicator)).Count\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    $total = $invariantCount + $variantCount\r\n    $invariantRatio = if ($total -gt 0) { $invariantCount / $total } else { 0 }\r\n    \r\n    $analysis += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n        Pulse = $pulse.Name\r\n        InvariantCount = $invariantCount\r\n        VariantCount = $variantCount\r\n        InvariantRatio = [math]::Round($invariantRatio, 3)\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n#\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 04:26:46\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774340823106}}
